I see two issues: 1) remove the `.ts` extension from the import, and 2) `/**` is invalid in version `'1'` due to wildcard rules. Let me use version `'1.1'` (the default) and fix the import.

Also, I need to reconsider why my previous tests passed on both. Let me think again about `/**` in version `'1.1'`:

The wildcard check for `'1.1'`: `/\*[^*/]|\+[^+/]|[^/*]\*|[^/+]\+|\*\*\*|\+\+\+/`

`/**` - does it match? `**` is two stars, not three. Let me check: `[^/*]\*` - the char before `*` in `/**` is `/`, so no match. `\*[^*/]` - after `**` is end of string, no match. So `/**` is valid in `'1.1'`.

